{"name": "kcolorconverter", "metadata": {"name": "kcolorconverter", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: MacOS", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Operating System :: Unix", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/kokaito-git/kcolorconverter", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A utility library for converting colors between formats like RGB, RGBA, HEX6, and HEX8. Provides flexible handling of color representations for Python applications.", "upload_time": 1734179527}, "documentation": [""], "modules": [{"name": "kcolorconverter", "documentation": ["KColorConverter: A library for converting colors between multiple formats.\n\nThis library provides tools to handle and convert colors between formats such as RGB, RGBA, HEX6, and HEX8.\nIt offers flexible handling of input formats (strings, tuples) and output specifications. Ideal for developers\nworking with color manipulations in Python.\n\nKey Features:\n- Convert between formats:\n  - RGB (e.g., (255, 0, 0))\n  - RGBA (e.g., (255, 0, 0, 1.0))\n  - HEX6 (e.g., #FF0000)\n  - HEX8 (e.g., #FF0000FF)\n\n- Customizable output formats:\n  - Use format strings like 'III' for integer output or 'IIIF' for mixed integer-float output\n    (e.g., (255, 0, 0, 0.5)).\n\n- Helper functions:\n  - Convert integer values (0\u2013255) to floats (0.0\u20131.0) and vice versa.\n  - Automatically determine format types when converting.\n\nClasses:\n- KColorFormat:\n  An enum representing supported color formats (RGB, RGBA, HEX6, HEX8).\n\n- KColorConverter:\n  The main class providing conversion methods and utilities.\n\nMethods:\n- KColorConverter.convert(color, output_type, fmt=None):\n  Converts a color to the desired output format.\n    - color: The input color as a string or tuple.\n    - output_type: The desired format (e.g., KColorFormat.RGB).\n    - fmt: Optional format string for output.\n\n- Helper methods (used internally but can be useful):\n  - int_to_float(value: int): Converts an integer (0\u2013255) to a float (0.0\u20131.0).\n  - float_to_int(value: float): Converts a float (0.0\u20131.0) to an integer (0\u2013255).\n  - _determine_format(values: Tuple): Determines the format string based on input types.\n\nExamples:\n# Convert a HEX color to RGB\nrgb = KColorConverter.convert(\"#FF5733\", output_type=KColorFormat.RGB)\nprint(rgb)  # Output: (255, 87, 51)\n\n# Convert a HEX color to RGBA with a custom format\nrgba = KColorConverter.convert(\"#FF5733\", output_type=KColorFormat.RGBA, fmt=\"IIIF\")\nprint(rgba)  # Output: (255, 87, 51, 1.0)\n\n# Convert an RGB tuple to a HEX6 color\nhex6 = KColorConverter.convert((255, 87, 51), output_type=KColorFormat.HEX6)\nprint(hex6)  # Output: \"#FF5733\"\n\n# Convert an RGBA tuple to a HEX8 color\nhex8 = KColorConverter.convert((255, 87, 51, 128), output_type=KColorFormat.HEX8)\nprint(hex8)  # Output: \"#FF573380\"\n\n# Convert an integer to float\nprint(KColorConverter.int_to_float(128))  # Output: 0.5019607843137255\n\n# Convert a float to integer\nprint(KColorConverter.float_to_int(0.5))  # Output: 128\n\nFor more examples, refer to the GitHub repository: https://github.com/kokaito-git/kcolorconverter"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "kcolorconverter.KColorConverter", "xref": {"fqname": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorConverter", "project": null}}, {"name": "kcolorconverter.KColorFormat", "xref": {"fqname": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorFormat", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorFormat", "bases": ["Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorFormat.RGB", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorFormat.RGBA", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorFormat.HEX6", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorFormat.HEX8", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Enum representing supported color formats.\n\nAttributes:\n    RGB: RGB format as a tuple (R, G, B).\n    RGBA: RGBA format as a tuple (R, G, B, A).\n    HEX6: Hexadecimal format without alpha (e.g., \"#RRGGBB\").\n    HEX8: Hexadecimal format with alpha (e.g., \"#RRGGBBAA\")."]}, {"name": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorConverter", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorConverter.convert", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "color", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Num", "xref": {"fqname": "Num", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Num", "xref": {"fqname": "Num", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Num", "xref": {"fqname": "Num", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Num", "xref": {"fqname": "Num", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Num", "xref": {"fqname": "Num", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Num", "xref": {"fqname": "Num", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Num", "xref": {"fqname": "Num", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "output_type", "type": {"name": "KColorFormat", "xref": {"fqname": "kcolorconverter.kcolorconverter.KColorFormat", "project": null}, "params": null}